text: Great food at a great price generous portions can not go wrong here.

I was only in town for a couple of days and was looking for a good sit down pizza place where I could have a drink. This place was perfect, appetizers and pizza were delicious and Berenice gave great service
Cute, low key corner shop. Very chill and the salads surprisingly delicious. Normal SF pricing ($15 per salad), though portion size is a bit smaller than expected. Got the house salad.
The salads are outstanding, thanks to the fact that Davon makes about the best salads I’ve ever had.
Delicious Colombian coffee, amazing cakes and wonderful staff!

Ordered from the menu, was charged more and told that the prices are almost current. The woman insisted that I pay the new price which wasn't written anywhere and refused to acknowledge the menu price.
One of the top choices in the DMV area. All-around service and quality.
Good food for a great price in SF!

Great service, friendly staff, DELICIOUS food! First time at Mixto and it did not disappoint. We went there for dinner and ordered ceviche mixto, birria taco’s and arroz con mariscos. The portions are very generous (two people couldn’t finish a starter, ceviche and a main, took some of it home) and everything is freshly made which makes them very flexible when it comes to food restrictions. I like the dim lighting because it made the dinner feel like date night on a Wednesday. Also, it is located in a quiet neighborhood which gives so much privacy and the time to properly enjoy your food without rushing to empty the table. Will visit them for brunch next time
Friendly staff and great noodle soup cooked to order.

The serenely decorated space of this restaurant caught our eye. The main attraction was the water cascading down the walls near the private canopies. It was definitely a delight to dine here as the atmosphere was aesthetically pleasing. Our table ordered the King Crab- steamed, with sauces on the side,  okra, Fried Calamari, Rice. The waitress brought out the Crab before it was cooked..I didn't realize how big it was but I got it any way. It was absolutely delicious .  The Okra was perfectly cooked, it still had a little bit of a crisp bite so it wasn't as slimy as you would think. The fried Calamari was cooked perfectly as well, it came with spicy mayo, which we enjoyed as well. I mean even the white rice was good. The customer service was impeccable as well. Overall a great dining experience.  Thank you yo all the staff that assisted us.

Update: Try their very good soup!! Be prepared to wait for your food. Not a quick lunch by any stretch. Allow extra time, or get there early. From the time I got in line to when I received my order of soup and salad — it was over 30 minutes. Pretty good lunch! The soup was very thick, (like stew) and spicy so I added some beef broth I had a my office. Today I tried the chicken salad. Not as good as the beef Barbados I had last time. They still do not have a very mild option on salsa. All of the salsa choices were hot. Still Very busy and seating was hard to come by. The line was about 10 people deep when I showed up just after 12 on a Wednesday for lunch. Employees are friendly but seemed overwhelmed both times. Go outside of lunch hours, if you can. Today I did not feel the food made up for the long wait time. I don’t usually have a full hour for lunch.

These were some of the best empanadas we have ever had! We originally stopped here as part of a food tour. The food was so incredible that we stopped by again for lunch the next day! Everything is made fresh, and there is a quite a variety of empanadas to try! If we're ever back in Dallas, this spot is on our list of must visit!

Salvio's has incredibly delicious food and their service is excellent.  My mom has sent me surprise pizzas at the pharmacy and they write a note from her on the inside of the box.  They deliver it with a smile because they know it's a surprise and I'll probably cry.
Anna delivered mine today and it was delicious as usual.
Best evening/night crew in drive thru window...funny kids;)

The food is good but they had us waiting 2 HOURS for our order. They emailed saying our food was ready for pickup and when we got there we were waiting an hour. The service is horrible! I don’t recommend going there unless you like poor timing and service.

This real mexican restaurant has changed its name to Martinez taqueria.
By real mexican restaurant I mean traditional cuisine. It tasted like my grandmother was cooking.
I mentioned to my wife that I felt like having huitlacoche(a mushroom that is harvested from corn) she asked at her work and someone mentioned the restaurant by it's former name.
I had a gordita with chicharrón en salsa verde while waiting for my huitlacoche quesadilla. The gordita was light tasting with a slight crunch  but filled with chicharrón and cotija cheese. The huitlacoche quesadilla was HUGE about 20 inches long filled with cotija cheese, chopped onions and of course tons of huitlacoche. Table side they have salsa roja and salsa verde. I WILL RETURN TO SAMPLE THE REST OF THE MENU!

OMG!! Do you want to talk about a great place to get something to eat from? Well then Lebowski's is the place to go to, my daughter and I went here for lunch and from the moment we walked in it was a vibe! The service was awesome the food was great and we will definitely be back again. I highly recommend stopping by if you ever get the chance to, because the food is definitely a 10 10 10!! Thank you so much for your great atmosphere and hospitality.

This is our favorite restaurant in New Orleans!! The Paneed Chicken is DELICIOUS. It is my husband and I's favorite food. The atmosphere is so relaxing and welcoming! The service is always lovely. We can't wait to visit each time we past through!!

When our large family gathers we like to have sombeody else do the cooking. Lately that somebody has been Bambinelli's takeout. We love the basics here - Chicken and Eggplant Parm with a side of pasta, Calzones, Pizza, Lasagna and especially the large family salads. There is something for everybody on the menu. We gather up our orders and then send a runner over since we live next door in Garden Hills. But we have also used the delivery service and were pleased. We started doing this during the CoVid lockdown and it is one of the few good things to come out of that time. Instead of paying a small fortune to go to a Buckhead restaurant we get great food served with our own beverages around big table at home. Babies get put to bed on time, conversations around the table linger and there always seems to be enough food for leftovers. Bonnie Bambinelli would approve.  Bada Bing.
Drive Thru was very busy. But food was good

Checked out some reviews before I went, oh my gosh I can not tell you how much I enjoyed the Catfish. The seasoning was great, big portions, staff was polite I will definitely be back again. Thank you

This was my first time to this restaurant and I was truly impressed with the level of customer service the taste of the food authentic Cajun experience. Menu had a variety healthy and good choices food was very tasty fish and shrimp was cooked to perfection I recommend the the two-piece Croaker West shrimp combo you won't be disappointed.

PLEASE it’s not hard to follow directions. Especially when I place an order, I can’t get a whole refund on delivery apps and the mistakes get very costly. Don’t just look at the name of an item when you’re preparing, PLEASE LOOK AT THE INSTRUCTIONS TOO FOR ADD ONS OR SUBTRACTIONS FROM THE ORDER.

I was a regular customer but no more. Theyre stingy and food is never consistant anymore. Also their menu prices is designed to make you order more than you should. In this economy, if youre going to charge people more for food then you should serve the right amount of food for it, not just stuff the container with rice and a lil amount of of whatever entre. The brisket had zero flavor other than the BBQ sauce they loaded on. The mac & cheese was the worst cheese sauce soup with boiled shells I have EVER had. Furthermore, it did not include all items listed  in the menu.  For a specialty menu item and the cost of the dish, I expected more. Very disappointed.

Don’t try to order out from them you will not get your food, not given updates, not answer the phone, not respond to you, and try and keep the money. I wish I could tell you how the food was but I wouldn’t know.

I have been to this Chick-fil-A four or five times since it opened about four months ago, and the experience has improved each time! They have a mostly brand new staff that is still learning, but the extremely negative tone of the reviews shared here does not match the quality of experiences I’ve had - The food was delicious, the staff was professional and attentive, the service was excellent and the store was clean!

As a former employee, I know Chick-fil-A has set the customer service bar high for its customers, and with this being a new location they certainly have room to grow in speed, accuracy and efficiency. However, to go a step further and demonize the community surrounding the store (as many reviews have done) is too far.

As you all know, Chick-fil-A traditionally operates stores in more affluent/middle class communities, and this particular store is located right on the boundary line between a high poverty neighborhood and a very affluent neighborhood in Charlotte. I can’t help but think this unique reality unfairly contributes to people’s perception of the store and its employees if the quality of service isn’t at the high standard they expect it to be.

In addition to providing great food and good service to customers, this store also provides over a hundred people with stable, high quality employment within walking distance of their homes. I’m not sure how many employees live in the community surrounding the store, but having employment options walkable to lower income residents is super rare in car-dependent cities like Charlotte, and it’s worth being excited about!

So don’t let these reviews keep you from giving this location a shot. Cut them some slack and give them some time to train their employees and develop them. And if the drive through line is long, park and walk in - 9 out of 10 times it’s faster anyway.

Thanks for reading - I’ll certainly be back!
Great crispy chicken! Just what we wanted. Thanks!

The best breakfast ever!! This is our go to for breakfast every visit to Orleans! Prices are reasonable and the food is cooked to perfection, especially those biscuits! Definately try this place out, you'll be back :)

Went back to Cafe Flora for some delicious Brussels Sprouts. They do a great job with social distancing in the restaurant. However, after sitting down for an hour, I was asked to leave because there were other people waiting for a table. After buying a full meal, coffee AND tipping 20% to the servers, I was asked to leave a restaurant because I was lingering. Unacceptable. Most people are not dining out often during Covid. So to be asked to leave a restaurant during your one weekly outing is not a great feeling. I may return for the Brussels Sprouts, but I will get these to go, so I don't have to deal with the terrible customer service.

Recommend

Was closed and a pod was at the front door .. appear to be moving or closing up!

Wow what an experience! From the hostess to the chef our experience was phenomenal. Went for the omakase experience and will be back for sure. We were greeted by a very kind hostess who took our coats and led us to the bar while we waited for our sever- the bar was attentive, quick and very friendly even offering suggestions based on our usual drink types. Our server came to greet us at the bar and walked us to the Omakase area which was so beautiful — the details of the restaurant were just perfect.

Once we sat down our server went over the drink pairing with us and we opted to let him choose for us throughout the dinner (excellent decision). The chef came out to greet us and immediately started preparing fresh wasabi and getting right into the meal.

The food was delicious. They have a unique sushi experience with dry aging the fish. We were able to compare fresh and dry aged of multiple types and then moved on to Nigiri (and wow this was my favorite part). Everything we ate was delicious and we left very satisfied and will be back.

We didn’t take many photos as we were living in the moment but this place needs to be added to your must try date night spots ASAP.

I booked this venue for Valentine’s Day with my wife. $85 per person is reasonable so I booked it. We were greeted promptly and politely by the hostess. The restaurant was basically empty, which made me wonder why the booking time was so limited. It took a few minutes to be greeted and offered drinks, but the bar was busy so we understood. When we placed our order, we watched our drinks sit on the bar for 8 minutes before my wife got up and got them for us. When it came time to order from the fixed menu, I was concerned when they didn’t ask what temperature I wanted my filet. Come to find out, it’s only well done. They brought out my plate with mushrooms, some sort of potato, and a thin filet cooked WELL DONE. It was painfully obvious the steak was premade and microwaved to order. My wife got scallops and risotto, the scallops had a strong fishy smell to them, which is NOT in the norm. I sent my steak back to be prepared medium rare as a filet should be. The product they returned to me was BLUE RARE at best. At this point, I was annoyed. So I asked them to return the food and bring us our check. I gladly paid for my wife’s meal since she tolerated the scallops. The oxtail pie appetizer was bland, and the cappuccino tomato soup starter was good, but was maybe an ounce. To top it off, they brought h wife her dessert and sent back mine since I returned my meal, and requested it to be removed (I took one bite of my well done steak). While I understand they shouldn’t just hand stuff out, they should have at least made an effort to remedy the poor food quality. I don’t blame the server at all. Either way, I paid $113 for my wife’s meal that was mediocre at best. The risotto was bland and overcooked along with the overly fishy scallops. I hope management fixes this for future diners. Luckily, we found an Italian place down the street to eat.
Brandon knows what he’s doing behind the bar!

One of my favorite places in NYC.

The secret to the success of this establishment is the staff. They are hard working, attentive, and always make you feel welcomed, like family. Bartenders usually know what you are drinking when you come back the 3rd time and are always quick to serve, even when there is no space at the bar. Some must haves on the tapas are the empanadas, mofonguitos, pulpo, tostones and chorizo, bacon wrapped dates, canastitas de bacalao, for mains the churrasco, paella and salmon are amazing.

We prefer to not dress up too much and sit in the bar area, and have always loved every minute of it. We didn't order wine and my wife wasn't too hungry so only ordered a salad and a side dish, and the waitress didn't seem to be happy about that and didn't pay much attention to us. Also the bar area is calm and laid back but both dining are as loud as a high school cafeteria and for some reason no one even tries to keep their voices down. AVOID this restaurant!!! One of worst dining experiences ever. We had reservation at 05:30 for 5 people and when arrived we were told to head to bar had a mix up for our table. No one ever came to get us after said would just be a few minutes . We headed back up to hostess desk after waiting for amount of time we were told. We stood another couple minutes in the line near hostess desk and were finally called. The hostess desk is very unorganized and whole reservation system is very poorly managed. We headed to our table at 05:50 we didn’t get waited on until 06:20 and this was after several waiters walked by and the large table behind us sat after us and got waited on before us . We waited over an hour for our food and we had to have someone from our table go to host desk and inquire about order because our waitress disappeared. She then came by table after inquiring about order and told our ticket was up next it was an hour and ten minutes to get four entrees. I understand delays happen but your staff shows no care or concern . We talked to “kitchen manager “ and host at desk and they showed no concern. No manager ever came by table to check in which is so bizarre . After stating how long waited for food the waitress said can offer dessert on the house. After one of us said just take their one entree off before we got food, she had to realize we waited too long. At this point we just wanted to leave it was ridiculous it took that long as other people that sat after us and only had 2-5 people in party and had over 5 tables  around us that got food before us. This establishment is severely lacking in customer service, hospitality and atmosphere. Stay away unless you want to have bad dining experience and poor customer service. Lastly, tried to contact restaurant thru their  email listed on website and email does not even work! It got returned as undeliverable email address  . Although i gave this place 5 stars, it's for all the other times I've gone. All the food has been good. However, the satellite this is it @ the market place has fallen off with the potato salad the last 2 times I've been. The potato salad has been liquidity and the taste is off. Please fix this.
JOSE THE BARTENDER IS BACK.  Off Monday and Wednesdays.  Confirmed 12/20/2023!

Happy to have a nice breakfast before we left
Nice service , friendly and smiles
Tooo expensive for fried chicken and same goes for the pizza….

Had an Omelette with mushrooms and other vegetables, which were served raw and undercooked.  It was dry and tasteless.  The breakfast potatoes were also undercooked.  The outside area upstairs was nice.  Service was average.

Look, there are limited options at Midway. You don’t come here expecting a 5-star restaurant. You deal with what you got. Gene’s just happens to be here. HOWEVER, Jason T was our waiter here and this guy crushed it. He was slammed busy and still took care of his entire section with a smile on his face. Absolutely crushed it. Shoutout Jason T. Now that I think about it, this place should be called Jason’s.
Forgot mu mash potatoes in the first order. Then I came back today and they gave me the wrong type of tenders three times.

I called to complain about my order apparently you get a spoon full of asada meat on a chilaquiles plate almost paid $20 to get so little these restaurants want to raise prices even charge you service fee for a minimal effort platter never again WENT to a restaurant called a chilaquil for the same platter more steak and more to offer as u can see the picture on the righ under the zacatacos make your money worth it go to el chilaquil paid 16 for their platter located on southwest highway
Great meal easy atmosphere.

We arrived around 2:30.. didn’t put in food or drink orders until 2:50. It was maybe 10 people in the whole restaurant. So very unsure why service was awfullllllllly slow. We had the scallops app & a side of fruit (best thing we had there). Ordered the Carmel Old Fashioned… meh. Also, ordered a mocktail.. yuck. From there, we ordered Hanger Steak & Tenders & fries for our daughter.. we didn’t recieve that until 3:45. Again, there’s 10 people in the restaurant. Everyone just moves around like they’re on edibles. It’s so underwhelming. I’ve never had to ask for a Togo box before the food came & still ended up leaving the food because it was just bad. Hanger steak was lukewarm & the tenders were fried hard & sat under the heating lamp on expo for about 10 minutes. Such a waste of money. Lost our appetite & going home to take a nap to sleep off my horrible mood.

This Mexican food is good every single time -no lie. They legit don’t have bad days, this family puts their everything into the food and you can taste it🫶

The burritos are AMAZING and I’ve been told they take people back to CA lol
Good food and service!
Incredible place! Amazing food! I heard the owner's son drives a sweet Japanese sports car too!

First Time ordering from here and I was up @ 5 in the morning throwing up.
Nope ‍
Love their chicken Pho on a rainy day or to restore myself

I highly recommend going to ANOTHER SUBWAY , the lady worker is so stingy with the food being provided! She barely gives you anything on your sandwich and charges extra for a little bit more ! Save your time and get what your moneys worth SOMEWHERE ELSE!

Every time we come here, we are treated with so much respect and excellent service! The food is always done to perfection and the drinks are spectacular—everything prepared with precision and love. Coming here feels like HOME! Always good vibes. However, I wanna do a quick shoutout to ED who we had the pleasure of meeting today. I am not even done with my meal yet and am just blown away by his incredible spirit, passion for service, heart of gold, sense of humor, professionalism, kindness, and leadership skills. This guy should be not only running this restaurant, but should be in charge of training all new hires within the region. People like him take a restaurant and make it a destination for good vibes, conversation, and a home away from home. Protect him at all costs and give him a generous raise!
Also, this location is in SUCH a great location right next to the subway, Target, Marshall’s and more. Incredible happy hour. 10 stars all around.

I walked all the way from my hotel and you were closed earlier than expected with no notice. Your small business needs to do better in the professionalism that it provides in communication with their customers.

If your looking for some good authentic, Caribbean cuisine in the Boston area.I highly recommend checking out Fusion Caribbean kitchen.I had the Fry Sweet Chilli Shrimp and Chowmein Noodles with Sweet Chili Salmon
Omg John Piazza makes the best drinks ever! Love this place

Been coming here for almost 21 years since I turned 20 years old in 2003 and have usually had very good experiences here except a few times in 2019 but fortunately the staff has really changed and improved since then and the manager is really friendly. I usually don't eat fast food since it is not good for me, but I come here about once every 2 months for the veggie whoppers. Taste great but I am careful not to get too addicted to it! Moderation is key!

Definitely complain that you’ve waited too long and a manager will seat you before others who have waited longer than you. Same party of 3. Still waiting. Haven’t eaten yet and we left because after being seated after 1 hr, we were told the wait for food would be 1 hr. It’s now 1p and they close at 2. Not happy with this eatablishment
To bad this place closed was lit
The food was very tasty and filling. I requested delivery and it was delivered within a reasonable time and neatly packed. The hot honey sauce is amazing!! My new healthy go to, fast food spot.

The food was amazing. This is a new spot in Buckhead that should be experienced. The music was great and the staff was awesome. The owner was in the building and personally came by our table to make sure everything was good. I will be back.

If you’re in the market for a true foodie experience, this is the place! From the warm welcome as  you walk through the door, to the way they took the time to explain the delightful menu options, it’s really easy to fall in love with Phat Yuca.

I had the HellaVegan with a side of sweet potatoes drizzled with the mouthwatering white garlic sauce. Truly an explosion of flavors! The yuca pocket literally melts in your mouth...downright delicious!

Between the friendly service, the savory menu and the chill music, this place is a total VIBE!

We were staying in the neighborhood on a trip and wanted something to eat for the family that wasn't burgers or fried chicken tenders. This place was great! All the sides were hot and tasty and it was a great value for us and our kids. Plenty of parking as well.

I was so excited about trying this place, but unfortunately, I didn’t get the opportunity to. The woman behind the counter wouldn’t let me get a word in edgewise. I found her to be quite rude and condescending as she was explaining the menu, which I told her that I had already looked at online to familiarize myself with. Im already familiar with vegan cuisine, which I’ve been eating and preparing since the 1980s. I feel like there’s a lot of cultural appropriation going on here and that’s not cool either but be that as it may, someone needs cultural/ethnic sensitivity training to go along with the food. The decor and space is nice and bright, a little awkwardly shaped but they seem to be making best of the space. Note to self: any time AAVE is being used in the menu and advertising, caveat emptor.
Overpriced hotel bar.
I would give it three stars but the guy at the drive thru line was rude.
Great ambient.... excellent service
Good food

Went their for buffet breakfast wanted to have Avocado toast they said they were out of it .
Everything was hot, food was good i got the fresh beignets and we enjoyed it very much .
Stopped on for breakfast: chicken and waffles,  smoked salmon bagel and crawfish quesadilla with sides of grits and a sausage.

Tiny place on the corner. I called in my first time order and it was ready when I got there 10 minutes later. I purchased 2 Pu Pu platters and everything was delicious. Ribs were tender and perfect. I will definitely be back. 2 thumbs way up for this place. Just remember its cash only! There is an ATM next door at the convenience store.

RAW BACON. We ordered deviled eggs and the “bacon” deviled eggs came with RAW bacon. I told the server who then told me it’s procuitto.. when it’s obviously bacon and the menu says it’s bacon too. They then brought out the deviled eggs with cooked bacon and the eggs are cold and hard. Its obvious they didn’t remake the deviled eggs as you can see the indent from the raw bacon. I lost my appetite and told the manager to just take this away. He stormed away while I was in mid sentence and said we just took it off. No apology just a lot of sass. We stayed at this hotel too and this was a horrible experience. Would never recommend.
This place is a health hazard! My sister got food poisoning after eating here. We are looking up who to contact and report this to. They need to do better!

honest to god I have never written a bad view but this is the biggest waste of your money in town, I couldn’t even ingest a single bite of my entrée. which feels crazy to say! it’s truly that bad. server was nice though.

Just had one of the worst experiences. I was doordashing and when I walked in, it took quite a while for someone to help. Three employees looked at me and said nothing. I finally had to walk behind the register to my order in order to get some help. IRIS, who I asked more than once if I could get some help, but got nothing as she finished a conversation with someone sitting in an office, finally makes her way to the register to confirm my order Lastly, my drink order was wrong. When I pointed that out, IRIS looked at me as if I was crazy. She then says, "We don't have Dr. Pepper back here." Instead of IRIS walking 50 feet to get the order right nor providing a cup, I had to ask for a cup to get the correct drink for my customer! Like, wow!! What happened to plain old customer service?!! If yall don't want to work, then don't please! As I was walking out, the manager, I assume dressed in all black, came out but didn't say thing. SMH!!
They have a variety of ice creams to choose from.
I don't eat meat.  I bought it for someone.  But she was enjoying it so much that her and her kids were humming and eating 🤣🤣🤣

Go to the 95th location!!!!!
Denied me paying over the phone after they denied my brother who I sent with my card to pay. The worker over the phone hung up while I was asking a simple question and stated “we’re closing” then hung up. If you aren’t closed and I ordered wait for me to talk. The food is also not worth the effort so never again you should really work on your people skills. And check the account I usually give great reviews but this was by far some of the worst customer service . Do Better!
Love this wee spot. Consistently good food. Ok service. Ok atmosphere. Nice outdoor seating, too.
Picked up some tacos and churros from here today and they were DELICIOUS! Definitely gonna be coming back here.
One of my favorite pizza spots in the city.
Hostess was rude as soon as we walked in. Food was delicious, aside from the shell pieces in the lobster roll. Our bartender was great.

We've been coming here religiously ever since we moved to Charlotte, and it's the first place we suggest when we have people visit. I've never had a bad meal here. The food is always delicious, and the Well-Fed platter is one of the best deals in town. The only complaint I have is that they are missing a southern staple: fried okra. That would make it an 11/10.
The Buffalo chicken pizza is straight fire!! Absolutely delicious.

I got takeout for my family.  The person over was extremely nice and very helpful with my order.  When I got to the restaurant my food was packed and ready to go and the cashier was happy to add a drink for me.

The atmosphere when I entered was very in line with their sign saying they'd been open since 1933.  The lighting was perfect.  Everything was clean and I'd say half of your meal was the experience of eating there.

We got a burger with onion rings, chicken tenders with fries, and quesadillas with sweet potato fries, and two cheeseburger sliders.  The total was about $70.  So about $15 per meal and $10 for the sliders.  Which is pretty much in line with food from a restaurant these days.

I enjoyed my sweet potato fries.  I did need to add a little salt.  My quesadilla was enjoyable but not great.   I would ask for the salsa and sour cream to be separate because they were together. It also could have been crispier and had more than just cheese and chicken.  I did ask for chicken and steak but it was just chicken.

My mother-in-law enjoyed her cheeseburger with lettuce, tomato, grilled onions, Swiss cheese and mushrooms.  She enjoyed her meal and ate her leftovers.

My husband got chicken tenders with fries.  The fries he called ok.  He didn't eat them all and didn't finish them later.  We did hear them up and they would have been better fresh I think.  There were a lot of tenders about six.  They were thin for restaurant tenders and my husband said they were over cooked.  He called them passable but did eat the rest later so they were edible.

We got onions that nobody ate.  They looked a little burnt.  The sliders were your common sliders they weren't anything special but they were cooked well.

I would recommend eating in because the food would have been better fresh and I think the restaurant's atmosphere would have made up for the ok food.
This is a really good Soul food Restaurant, With welcoming customer service!!! I recommend this place to anyone.
Just ate there for the first time and the Asian salmon bowl was delicious! Great service too :)

The spaghetti and meat sauce was really yummy. The portions are very generous for the price. The person at the pickup window was so nice and friendly. They had nice music playing and the atmosphere was welcoming. The placing order/pickup process was seamless. I’ll definitely be checking out more on the menu.
Door says lobby is open until 10 but doors are locked at 8

Edit: Things have improved a lot now. Blaze continues (Holly Springs) to suck as usual

I and family are a regular here and prefer over Blaze but lately they seem to be running out of toppings frequently. Can't enjoy a pizza when your favorite toppings are missing. Will probably move back to blaze.At least we get what we want.
Tha chicken was good taste and juicy , and the lady on the counter was really attentive

Service: went on a Friday night, no wait. There is a live singer. Service is pretty quick, for two people we were only there for an hour.

Food/Beverage: we ordered the mango margarita & blue Hawaiian, both which were fantastic and not too strong. We dinner we ordered the bean sopes & the Enchiladas de Mole, both which were great! The salsa served with the chips was also fire

Ambiance: I didn't like how loud the singer was because I couldn't talk to the person I came with. Cute restaurant otherwise with street parking
The grease weighed more than the meat did on my barbacoa tacos.. meat also tasted out of date. Ended up chunking 4 tacos and eating the 20 bucks I spent instead

Stopped by from out of town, the kids were craving Pho and this place got good reviews.  We were disappointed to say the least. Went in didn't get service for quite some time, when the server finally came we were never offered water or drinks and he didn't clean the table which was dirty from the previous customer. We waited a long time to order, our appetizer never came, the pho came out with no limes and the jalapenos were cut huge. Like one jalapeno cut into 4 large peices. Then we asked for fish sauce because the pho needed it. The staff didn't know what fish sauce is. What kind of vietnamese restaurant doesn't know what fish sauce is? Finally got some limes and fish sauce after explaining to the all non vietnamese staff what it is. Once the Pho was flavored with fish sauce and lime it was acceptable.  We can't say anything about the other dishes because they never brought them but I wouldn't recommend this place to anyone who likes service in a restaurant.
Diverse menu and unique seating in the heart of Flushing
Absolutely love the curry chicken here because it's actually spicy. Can't find many Chinese restaurants that come out actually spicy! Fried chicken wings are great too!

Der Service hier ist nicht perfekt und als Mitarbeiter, der nur 30 Minuten Pause hat und begrenzte Zeit zur Verfügung steht, würde man denken, dass sie das Essen etwas schneller zubereiten würden. Aber ehrlich gesagt werde ich weniger als 10 Minuten haben, um das Essen in meinem Mund hinunterzuschlingen wie ein dicker Amerikaner.

Basically, customer service here is poor and unprofessional and unreliable. They are obvious when it comes to ignoring your questions or concerns. The women up front have an attitude majority of the time. They will talk smack about you once you walk away whether they helped you or ignored you and just stood there aimlessly when you’re trying to talk to them. Staff here will also attempt to accuse you of dining and ditching if you are by yourself and need to go to the bathroom and go back to your table. It’s absurd. Please choose somewhere else to eat.

Meh. Crust on pizza wasn't good. Sauce came from a can. No meat on the sandwich.
Drink was good. Atmosphere is nice.

I'm a Long time customer to this location. Love the food but after tonight,  they lost a customer. Ordered a medium pizza with bbq wings. They sent regular wings with hot sauce on the side. I called back and the option were a refund or an exchange. I asked for refund and they were going to come pick up the wings. Perfectly find with me.  However, the gentleman on the phone started to joke around on the phone while I was giving my information. He even had the the nerve to compare me to previous customers that tried to rip them off. Good food will never be worth disrespect and poor customer service.

The most unprofessional, lackadaisical, rude and badly managed places I’ve ever seen. The inside is almost always closed and when it isn’t they’re not capable of running a drive through and taking orders at the register at the same time. You may spend 20+ minutes in line and be the only customer in the building
The environment is bubbly, the people serving are so patient, and the food is delicious and at a reasonable price. What’s there not to love?

First time guests last night. Saw the recent negative reviews but decided to make my own assessment.
Turns out they’re accurate.

Service was sub-par. None of the staff looked like they even wanted to be there. Our server for some reason seemed irritated at what all of us ordered…why? Lol
The meatballs looked and tasted like they were frozen from a bag. The sauce was alright though.
Bread and “great olive oil” was far from great.
The Caesar was dry, and had 1 little anchovy on it. Pizza was ok.
The cacio e Pepe was wayyyyy undercooked and the cheese clumped (cheap ingredients)
And all of it was definitely overpriced for the quality.
However, the octopus was probably some of the best I’ve had in awhile.

I like the open kitchen but I still wouldn’t go back.

I wouldn't know how the food was because I was completely ignored. I went this evening for a bite, asked the host if I could sit at the bar and eat, he said yes. I sat down and was ignored for at least 5 min, the bar was not busy at all there were maybe 6 people total including myself! FInally a woman came up to me said hi and I asked if I could see a menu, she gave me one and proceeded to clean up around me, helped several other patrons at the bar, I sat there another 5-7min with NOTHING in front of me, not even offered a water! I finally just left after I saw 4 men being attended to, they already had drinks and water! Then I saw another man being offered a refill on his wine to seats awsy from me, I was thinking this cannot be real, do they not see me? There was three people behind the bar. This was offensive and will spread the word not to bother going if your a woman eating alone, plain and simple rude and uncalled for. I was there early in the evening the dinning room wasn't even a little busy. In total I waited almost 15 min to see if anyone would come and apologize and take my order. Don't waste your time!

I ordered my burrito then sat down and decided to check the reviews. Was a little concerned with the score. To my surprise my food was delicious and pretty good size burrito. So if you look at th score before coming in pleas give this place a shot. You won't be disappointed

I legit just asked the dude who made my sandwich for cheese, apparently he put it on there but I didn't see. I was kind and calm I asked the woman who was putting ny topings on next for some cheese and got yelled at by the man saying I ALRRADY PUT CHEESE ON THERE ITS MELTED. Like clearly was aggravated  by me asking for more cheese. It was beyond unexpected and completely rude. I only go to this subway because I work in the building otherwise I wouldn't go here again. The women have never treated me wrong but today the man really had my nerves going. I get scared when people yell at me and I shouldn't be yelled at for asking for cheese lmao unprofessional as idk what.
CLOSED FOR GOOD FRIDAY. Made the trek out here and they are closed.
Really good. Great service. No line.
I love this places , I enjoyed

Employee was so nasty, not smiling, don’t care. I really don’t understand why she is there making everybody unhappy. she probably had a fight at home with her husband. Shrimp was cold and French fries were soggy so I asked for fresh new ones and she gave me after about a 10 minute wait but it was a mixture of old and new fries.
More of a lounge the services brunch, still nice atmosphere.
great store
Lol could’ve made the loaded fries at my house for 10$ or less but The wings are good! decent size worth the price would come back for wings

After our first caterer fell through for our wedding, Beaucoup Eats helped us put together a buffet style menu and got us all set up for our wedding. They were so friendly and professional and had great communication throughout the planning process. The set up, food, and service was incredible! The price was very reasonable compared to other catering options, and the quality was top tier. It was so nice being able to share authentic Louisiana food to the brides family from California. We highly recommend using them for any catering needs and stopping by to try their unique dishes!
Food is good and really doesn’t have any complaints. Would suggest you order your food during lunch hour just in case, cause there will be at wait or line!!!
The cheesteakes taste milky and horrible. The food is gross The owner is really rude as well!
Best
Fantastic restaurant. Wonderful food & excellent service

Beautiful venue, incredible service, and most importantly the food is delicious. We came for brunch and there was a wide variety of options. The shrimp Creole here with the scallion pancake was the best shrimp creole I’ve had while in NOLA.

Decent food, prices increased and the younger lady at the cash register is rude most of the time. The older man and woman are nice, but their daughter is rude and will make them lose business. She is always upset and lacks good customer service.

They recently scaled back the menu, which would be fine if it was for the sake of increasing the quality of the food. Unfortunately, in addition to there being fewer options, the food is also worse. Even the tater tots aren't as good anymore. Really disappointed in the drop in quality recently.

I ordered a simple item to go, hashbrowns all the way. I paid $7+ and I expected a meal, what I got was half the portion I'm used to get and no chili at all. I'm extremely disappointed that the staff didn't let me  know they were out of chili. In the end all I got was an overpriced snack.
Our Server TJ was awesome, she did not hesitate to make sure we were good on everything. Her service is A1

The pasta is spectacular! And the meat was so tender it melted in my mouth! What a nice dinner I had at this place! without passing up the excellent attention of the staff there! It was a good experience! The atmosphere was also very different and beautiful!
the menus was really. tasty and really nice and clean served

I stop yesterday at 615 am for breakfast and the guy said they barely just got there and that nothing was ready. According to Google they open up at 530 am. This is thru out the week as well. I believe an update for hours of operation in due.

Best Bojangles I have ever been to! I was even missing an item from my order and staff was very nice and replaced the item.
Restaurant was super cleaned and staff were very attentive to keeping it looking good!
I ordered a Philly cheesesteak Papadia and the meat was uncooked at all and it had lot of cheese and the bread was burned.. step up your game bruh
Great food!

My boyfriend and I were at union station to catch a train and decided to stop at unos for pizza and a pitcher of beer. We were seated immediately and the hostess was really nice!

Unfortunately, it went downhill from here. The waiter told us he would be right with us continuously as we watched tables of people who came in after us get served.

Thinking maybe the waiter forgot about us, we moved to the bar, hoping for better service. It was the same. The bartender even poured a drink for someone who ordered one after us after we were still waiting and had been waiting over 15 minutes for the pitcher (we never got the pitcher).

We ended up just leaving. Dont eat here. The food court has way better service.

The food was delicious. We all had breakfast, chilaquiles.  The portion of the added protein (chorizo in one pork in the other) must increase if they want return customers. While favor is on point if your meat is all of a teaspoon you feel robbed.
Pretty sure they forgot my friends plate, arrived 15 minutes late.
Had a fun time walking the town
The  sides are amazing and the meat is super tender
Excellent food and great service. A gem in the city!

This place was nothing short of amazing. Sherlin’s service was exceptional. The ramen and the specialty cocktails were some of the best I have had in a long time. Recommend this place if you want a great experience with the utmost exceptional service. Will come again.
Bueno
Horrible service steak was over cooked. Was really close to other tables could barely walk by.
This establishment is laughable; restroom access is limited to employees, excluding paying customers, and the service quality is below standard.
Great food! Gumbo is so damn good!! Great customer service also
The owner of the catering company was excellent. Her kindness and delicious food was amazing! We liked the pasta the best! It was Creamy, vegetables were cooked well and so good!!

This is an intimate setting with an amazing atmosphere. The food is top notch and the services is remarkable. The owner is always present and she ensures your food is just what you ordered. They make you feel like you are at home! 🫶
Great table and waitress but what was happening in the kitchen??? Lumpy grits.  Terribly dressed salads.  Poorly presented plates.  There are better options in this great town.

A local delight!  I especially love the farmers chicken salad for lunch also don’t miss their chili, it hits the spot on a cold winter day. And you simply must go on a weekend and order their breakfast. They have some specialty items that are just amazing!

For lunch they know how to get you in an out so you’re not there past your lunch hour. Their service is always friendly and helpful and their answer to everything is  “Sure we can do that”
Maria is a sweet and kind woman with good customer service well done
Slow service. Infact very few staffs

The chicken sandwich and nuggets were so salty and greasy that we couldn't even finish them. The grease was litterly running down my husband's hand. I have high blood pressure, and the nuggets were too salty to eat. We were going to share the fries, but they were loaded with salt also. The food had no flavor, just tasted like grease!
Good food - my only complaint is this location doesn’t honor the “ Moe Monday” discount.
Great place and food, though we were able to finish only half of main dishes - too huge. ATM is one block away.

This is a cute little diner! The service was friendly and fast, food was delicious, and super reasonably priced. We had a large group and had struggled to find a place with enough seating, but they got us right in and it was great!

You can order ahead and I recommend you do so you don't need to wait too long. Oftentimes they get busy and don't pick up the phone the first one - three times you call, but just try again.

I recommend their cabeza if that doesn't gross you out. It's very tender and juicy.

They have a few parking spots in the back for pickup but the entrance is slightly hard to see.

The location is relatively clean and typical for this genre.
Great lunch! Recommend any of their sandwiches!
Trash establishment. Poor professionalism from the inception of my visit and poor customer service throughout. Food is subpar.  Avoid and go to other restaurants.

Food is gross, sits out all day, giving people food poisoning because they’re not making fresh food . It’s old and they don’t care as long as they get money . Place needs to be shut down with new management. Damn shame
Upscale dining with amazing dishes. Love it here. We sat outside on their patio, it was perfect. Service is very friendly, wine menu is great. Highly recommend for a special occasion.
Food was amazing. Got chili dog and chili cheese fries and loved every second.
Who knows when this place is open.  Google not correct, no information at the front or on the website…
Soooo good. Cheeseburger, chocolate shake, and onion strings. Can't beat it.
I loved it. They made my sisters birthday experience amazing. Definitely returning
Food tasted old. Not returning
The worst Wingstop ever
Local spot. No frills. Same people. Same food quality. It's good, consistent, dependable and affordable.

I went here to celebrate a friend’s birthday. We ordered the Maharani Mango Lassi, Moscow Mule, and a mango mocktail drink (name?). For appetizers, we ordered the Samosa Chaat and the Papdi Chaat. Those were so amazing! We ordered all three breads (naan, bhatura, and garlic naan), which were so good. I ordered the Tandoori Shrimp salad. My friend’s ordered the Chicken Tikka Masala Naanwich, the Shrimp Naanwich, the Peri-Peri Chicken Wings, and the Chicken Biryani. We loved everything!
Excellent service. Braised sliced fish was amazing
Y’all hit up Maria’s cabanas the lady in the back anna makes some good food and she is really good with the customers.
Good taste, quantity is average.  I had two dishes and both had little amounts of chicken. Pay for extra chicken and a side of vegetables if you like more.

I needed breakfast before heading out on the daily walk discovering New Orleans. The Vegan Huevos Rancheros were perfect for me: Everything I like and none of the things that banned by the doctor. More importantly,  really tasty with crunchy tortilla, red sauce and black beans.
Food was very spicy with lots of garam masala. I would recommend dailing it bit down a bit. Service was very good

Gave this place a try today cause I’ve been craving Egusi, let’s just say y’all hyped this place up! It taste like tomato soup with Cajun seasoning on top! Those of u who have never had authentic African food won’t get it! I’m annoyed cause this is the only African spot in Nola! 🤦‍

Fried pickles were good, chicken parm was ok. Didn't like the pasta portion of it though. Too creamy. Should of stuck to basic chicken parm with red sauce on the pasta. Food wasn't that hot coming out. Chicken in my daughter's Caesar salad wasn't horrible but could of been better. Creme Brule was delicious but you are served a very small amount in a small dish. The dish should of been deeper at least.

I got the brisket sandwich.  The meat was sitting in liquid and literally had no smoke flavor or anything.  The sandwich is $16.49 and they have the nerve to be using sweet baby rays bbq sauce.  How dare you charge that much and not even have housemade bbq sauce?!  The buns aren’t toasted either.  The older white lady was standoffish, and borderline rude.  She kept walking off on customers and not even acknowledging them except to say “what you getting?”  If you just have to eat try them, go for it. Henry's Majestic: A Disaster From Start to Finish

Starving after Church, Service Left Us Praying for Salvation

We arrived at Henry's Majestic with high hopes after hearing good things, only to be met with a nightmare of a dining experience. Let's just say our Easter celebration went from holy to "holy moly, this place is bad!"

Reservations Don't Mean Reservations

Despite having a reservation, our party of ten (including restless kids) waited a soul-crushing **hour and a half** for our food. By the time it arrived, we were famished and past the point of polite conversation.

A Sticky Situation (Literally)

A quick trip to the men's room did little to improve our mood. The floor was a disgusting tribute to those who came before us, leaving a lingering question about the overall cleanliness of the establishment.

Food? More Like a Food Quest

The agonizing wait for our entrees wasn't the end of the saga. After finally getting our food, it took another **45 minutes** just to receive a measly dessert.  Apparently, patience is a key ingredient at Henry's Majestic, because you'll need it in biblical proportions.

The Kitchen Gods Said "No" to My Friend's Meal

One member of our party never even received their dinner! Two whole hours vanished, and poof, no food appeared. The waiter's excuse of a "busy Easter rush" was laughable considering we had reservations. Shouldn't they have been prepared for a holiday crowd?

The Service? Non-Existent

Our waiter, Sam, tried his best, but  it wasn't enough to salvage this disaster.  There were no apologies, no attempt to fix the situation, just an acceptance of defeat.

The Last Supper (We Wish!)

This experience left a worse taste in our mouths than last year's fruitcake. Henry's Majestic is a place we'll be avoiding like the plague.  Save yourself the frustration and your hard-earned cash – take your Easter celebration elsewhere.

I was looking for a place to take my boyfriend for a celebration dinner, and this place had such a cool vibe on the pictures online and we love Asian food. The location is at a strip mall, so there's plenty of parking, and I promise the inside looks nicer than the outside. The inside is cool and modern, and the pictures of the lady on the wall look like my mom when she younger lol.

We came on a Wednesday evening and there was plenty of seating indoor, and at the bar, but we opted for outdoor seating since it was so nice out. I also saw a sign for a great happy hour deal, so I'll have to come back one day.

Let's start with the food. We ordered the Golden roll, and the pork belly buns, and both were delicious! For my entree, I had a Thai noodle dish that was extremely flavorful, while my boyfriend got the Korean rice bowl, which was not bad but not quite to the standard of the other dishes in our opinion.

Our service was not fantastic and was the only downside of our meal. Although our server was ok, she was a little crass and borderline curt, something that I would expect from a local dive bar, but not a nicer place like this. At first I chalked it up to her being young and similar in age to us so she might have been more informal to be relatable, but at the end when we asked for the check, I wasn't sure if I had finished my meal enough to need a box. She said that she was either bring a box now or not coming back, which I thought was a little rude and out of nowhere. Of course she never came back to check on us after that either even though we were still dining for another 20 minutes. It was just a sour way to end an otherwise nice dinner for a special occasion.

I was also shocked and a little offended to see a 30% tip option. Tipping has gone out of control and the guilt of selecting a more reasonable tip amount puts customers in an uncomfortable place, especially when the service was not great.

I'd love to come back to try more of the menu because we had a nice experience in terms of the food and atmosphere, but I would hope to have a different server if I were to come back.

My recent experience at Lemonade Restaurant left much to be desired, and various factors contributed to an overall lackluster visit. The food, including the chicken breast and salmon dishes, fell short of expectations, with a notable lack of flavor and a disappointingly dry texture. It was evident that the kitchen may have overlooked crucial elements that elevate a dining experience.

Adding to the disappointment was the sparse crowd; we were the only patrons at 7 pm on a Saturday night. This near-empty atmosphere was further highlighted by the visible departure of several potential diners who seemed unimpressed with the offerings. The lack of a bustling ambiance raised concerns about the restaurant's appeal and left us questioning our choice for the evening.

Unfortunately, the service didn't manage to salvage the experience. The servers appeared disinterested and failed to provide the helpful and attentive service one expects in a dining setting.

On a slightly positive note, the lemonade drinks offered a modest reprieve, providing a decent refreshment. However, they were not enough to counterbalance the subpar food and lackluster service.

In conclusion, Lemonade Restaurant's underwhelming food, poor service, and a conspicuously empty dining area on a Saturday night collectively painted a picture of an establishment struggling to meet expectations.

I googled Haitian restaurants nearby and spotted this one. I parked my car and said hmmmm this is a tiny place…hey let me try it anyways. I went in and the gentlemen behind the counter was so professional and kind. I’ve complimented him because in my opinion it is very hard to find an all around great Haitian restaurant or Haitian food business. I came in and didn’t know what I wanted. He walked me through making up my mind. He had patience, a great tone of voice, honesty, great listening skills and such a positive energy. This is exactly what ANY restaurant should be like.

The food was amazing - GREAT PORTION  I ordered du ri jon jon ( black rice - most people call it but the correct name is dried mushroom rice ) with legumes and baked macaroni and Soup Joumou! YUMMY !!!!!! The legumes was amazing because it didn’t have too much acid in it. Some places love to add acid or too much spice to the legumes but this one was perfect! The rice was amazing also because it was fully cooked. I really don’t like ordering this kind of dish or ANY and Haitian food that is not fully cooked! I applaud this place!

I rarely write reviews but when I do it’s serious! I would like to also say I applaud the owner for believing in him and hiring him. This man will go far in life. Please continue to support employees like him. I have to also give a round of applause to the people in the back who put their work in making the food as well. I just can’t write this review and forget the employees in the back. They are part of the business as well! It’s not easy waking up everyday cooking and serving people - it can be challenging. I applaud this place. For such a small place to eat-the service and food is amazing! This goes to say never judge a book by its cover. You never know the greatness it has.

Please continue to do well in the community. I appreciate your business!

Sincerely,

A loyal customer

A Culinary Gem - Pasta & Provisions on Providence Shines!

Rating:  (5/5)

Pasta & Provisions on Providence is a true Italian culinary treasure in Charlotte, and my recent visit left me utterly delighted with a delectable assortment:

1. Chicken Viennese: 
It was tender, and impeccably seasoned, the Chicken Viennese was an appetizing beginning to my meal.

2. Garlic Rosemary Fresh Pasta: 
The roasted garlic fresh pasta added an exquisite garlic twist to my dishes, elevating them to gourmet status.

3. Spinach Lasagna: 
This comforting spinach lasagna with its layers of pasta and creamy ricotta was a heartwarming delight.

4. Marinara Sauce: 
The marinara sauce, bursting with tomato goodness and herbs, provided the perfect base for my creations.

5. Meatballs: 
Juicy, well-seasoned, and a perfect match for the marinara sauce, the meatballs were a carnivore's dream.

6. Lobster & Crab Ravioli: 
Decadent and rich, the lobster & crab ravioli were a luxurious indulgence.

7. Freshly Grated Cheese: 
The freshly grated cheese added that authentic Italian touch, enhancing the flavors of my dishes.

And the sweet finale of my visit was the heavenly Tiramisu:

8. Tiramisu: 
The Tiramisu was an absolute delight, a perfect balance of coffee-soaked layers and creamy mascarpone. It rounded off my Italian feast on a sweet high note.

Beyond their top-quality products, the staff at Pasta & Provisions on Providence were incredibly helpful, offering cooking tips and recommendations tailored to my needs.

This charming store exudes warmth and is perfect for both experienced chefs and culinary newcomers. For an authentic taste of Italy in Charlotte, Pasta & Provisions on Providence comes highly recommended. It's a gourmet Italian experience that leaves you craving more. Bellissimo!
